<%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>


    <div class="p-4 p-md-5 mb-4 rounded text-body-emphasis bg-body-secondary">
        <div class="col-lg-6 px-0">
            <h1 class="display-4 fst-italic">Ready to Share Your Thoughts?</h1>
            <p class="lead my-3">Click the button below to create a new post and start sharing your ideas with others!</p>
            <a href="/create-new" class="btn btn-primary">Create Post</a>

        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row g-5">
        <div class="col-md-8">
            <h3 class="pb-4 mb-4 fst-italic border-bottom">
                Voices in Words
            </h3>

            <article class="blog-post">
                <h2 class="display-5 link-body-emphasis mb-1">Why Learning to Code is Essential</h2>
                <p class="blog-post-meta"><%= date %> by <a href="#">Mahin</a></p>

                <p>In today's digital-driven world, coding is no longer a skill solely for software engineers. From enhancing problem-solving abilities to opening up new career opportunities, coding is increasingly relevant in various industries. Here's why learning to code is a smart move for anyone looking to excel professionally and personally.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Develops Logical Thinking:</strong> Coding trains the mind to think critically and approach issues methodically. This logical mindset is helpful beyond programming, making it easier to tackle everyday challenges.</li>
                    <li><strong>Expands Job Prospects:</strong> Coding skills can make you a more attractive candidate in fields like marketing, finance, and design, where digital proficiency is often required. Companies value employees who can streamline workflows and analyze data.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Empowers Personal Projects:</strong> Whether you want to create a personal blog, develop an app, or start an online business, coding allows you to turn ideas into tangible projects.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>Overall, coding empowers you to better understand the digital world and gives you tools to succeed in an increasingly tech-focused future. Investing time to learn coding may just be one of the best decisions for your career and personal growth.
                </p>
                <hr>
            </article>

            <article class="blog-post">
                <% posts.forEach(function(post, index) { %>
                    <h2 class="display-5 link-body-emphasis mb-1">
                        <%= post.title %>
                    </h2>
                    <p class="blog-post-meta"><%= date %> by <a href="#"><%= post.user %></a></p>

                    <p>
                        <%= post.content %>
                    </p>

                    <div style="display: flex; gap: 10px;">
                        <form action="/edit?_method=put" method="post">
                            <input type="hidden" name="index" value="<%= index %>">
                            <button class="btn btn-outline-info rounded-pill">Edit</button>
                        </form>
                        <form action="/delete?_method=delete" method="post"
                            onsubmit="return confirm('Are you sure you want to delete this post?')">
                            <input type="hidden" name="index" value="<%= index %>">
                            <button class="btn btn-outline-danger rounded-pill">Delete</button>
                        </form>
                    </div>
                    <hr>
                    <% }); %>
            </article>

        </div>

